    <section>
      <h2>01 &nbsp; Introduction</h2>
      <p>
        This Privacy Policy describes how the <em>1</em> watch face application ("the App") handles information on your Wear OS device. We are committed to being transparent about how the App operates.
      </p>
      <p>
        By installing and using the App, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this policy.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>02 &nbsp; Information We Do Not Collect</h2>
      <p>
        The <em>1</em> watch face does not collect, transmit, or store any personal information. Specifically, the App does not access or collect:
      </p>
      <p>
        — Personal identification information (name, email, address)<br/>
        — Health or fitness data (heart rate, steps, calories)<br/>
        — Location data (GPS or network-based)<br/>
        — Device identifiers or advertising IDs<br/>
        — Usage statistics or analytics<br/>
        — Contacts, messages, or any other device content
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>03 &nbsp; How the App Works</h2>
      <p>
        The App functions solely as a watch face, accessing only the system time and date provided by your Wear OS device in order to display them on screen. This is standard operating system behaviour and does not constitute personal data collection.
      </p>
      <p>
        All display rendering occurs entirely on your device. No data is sent to external servers, third parties, or the developer.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>04 &nbsp; Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>
        The App does not integrate any third-party SDKs, analytics platforms, advertising networks, or external services. No data is shared with any third party for any purpose.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>05 &nbsp; Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        The App does not knowingly collect any information from anyone, including children under the age of 13. As no data is collected at all, the App is safe for use by all ages.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>06 &nbsp; Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        If this Privacy Policy changes in the future — for example, if new features are added that affect data handling — this page will be updated with a new effective date. We encourage you to review this page periodically.
      </p>
    </section>

